color_probs = {color: count / total_games for color, count in color_counts.items()}

# Predict the next color based on probabilities
next_color = random.choices(list(color_probs.keys()), list(color_probs.values()))[0]

# Calculate accuracy of each color
accuracy = {color: count / (total_games - sum([color_counts.get(op_color, 0) for op_color in color_counts if color != op_color])) for color, count in color_counts.items()}

print(&quot;Predicted next color:&quot;, next_color)
print(&quot;Accuracy for each color:&quot;, accuracy)
</code></pre>
<p>The script first calculates the probability of each color based on their occurrences. Then, it makes a prediction for the next color based on these probabilities.</p>
<p>Finally, it calculates the accuracy of each color - this is the percentage of games where the color occurred out of all other games where that color didn't occur.</p></div>

