e manipulate it, along with turn any item, along with other items into an invention on the spot. I can also grab any tiny parts of a surface/machine, and shoot it at my opponent.”, Cuphead said. “Cool! When do I get mine?!”, Mugman asked, jumping up and down. “Not soon.”, Lion said. “Alright gang, follow me.”, Lion added, before walking off. “Oh…”, Mugman said, before dragging his feet and following Lion. Eventually, they reach an old building. “Alright. Bendy and Mugman. This is your test to see how strong you are. Whoever can exorcise the curse first gets a treat, paid for by me.”, Lion said. “Wait, what? What about the finger?”, Mugman asked. “Well, we need to see if you’re capable. So, like I said.”, Lion said. “Me and Cuphead here will spectate. Head on inside, and get that curse.”, Lion said, before sitting down. “Alright. See if you can keep up, Mugman!”, Bendy yelled, before in the blink of an eye, he dashed inside. “Woah, how did he move so fast?! Bendy can barely run within six feet of him without passing out!”, Mugman shouted. “It’s one of the additions that come with being a sorcerer. You also get your other physical feats leveled up the more cursed energy you have.”, Lion said. “Man…”, Mugman said, before quickly running inside. “You know…”, Cuphead said. “Mugman may die in there, Lion.” Lion glanced at Cuphead, before turning back and saying, “He’s strong. He’ll figure something out.” “And if he doesn’t?”, Cuphead asked. “We’ll help him.”, Lion said. We then cut to Mugman walking through the empty hallways of the building. “Man, this stinks. Figuratively and literally.”, Mugman said, as he was playing with Earth, Wind and Fire. Mugman then accidentally cuts his hand on Earth, Wind and Fire. “Ouch!”, Mugman said, as Earth, Wind, and Fire hit the ground. Then, suddenly, his wound heals, almost instantaneously. “Woah.”, Mugman said. Let me explain, real quick, to explain what happened. Mugman here just cut himself with a cursed tool. Cursed tools are imbued with cursed energy. Let’s just use numbers for an example. Let’s say that Earth, Wind and Fire has a cursed energy level of…two million. Not a lot for a cursed tool, but I’d say a little above average. When Mugman cut himself with Earth, Wind and Fire, he was imbued with…let’s say…half of that. So, he now has cursed energy, one million, to be exact. And, when he was imbued with the energy, he got so much a human couldn’t handle, that he reflexively performed Reverse Cursed Technique, which healed him. So, now Mugman can unlock his Cursed Technique, and become a sorcerer way earlier than he’s supposed to. But, he doesn’t know all this. Mugman stared at the wound, now healed. “That’s freaky.”, Mugman said to himself. Then,suddenly, he heard some groaning coming from another room. Mugman walked over to the room, to see a slug-like creature, or curse, staring at the clock. “WHAT…TIME IS IT?”, it said in a distorted voice. “It’s time…to get your butt kicked.”, Mugman muttered, before he pulled out Earth, Wind and Fire out of a knife holster on his leg. He dashed in the blink of an eye, behind the curse, and cut it in half, without even thinking. “WHAT THE SIGMA⁉️🔥🗣️🔥🗣️🗣️”, Mugman said, before he put back his weapon. “How did I-“, Mugman thought, before he heard Bendy walking towards the room, hearing the commotion. “Hey, Mugman, I heard a slash-“, Bendy said, before he saw the curse, cut in half. “…Say, Mugman…how did you defeat that curse…?”, Bendy asked. “I acted on instinct, I guess.”, Mugman said. “Instinct, huh?”, Bendy said. As quick as lighting, Bendy pulled out a sword, and swung at Mugman. Mugman, not even think, blocked it with Earth, Wind and Fire. “Let’s see how well you fight without any cursed energy.”, Bendy said, before he kicked Mugman into a desk behind him. Mugman avoided the desk and threw Earth, Wind and Fire at Bendy, before grabbing EWF (short for Earth, Wind and Fire), and slicing and dicing at Bendy several times at Bendy. “Don’t be scared. Close in.”, Mugman thought, as EWF and Bendys sword clashed multiple times. “Verb: Sharpen.”, Bendy said, before Mugman saw Bendys sword sharpen. Mugman kicked Bendys into a chalkboard, and continued to close in on bendy. Bendys grabbed some chalk by the chalkboard, and imbued it with some of his cursed energy, before saying, “Verb: Multiply. Verb: Sharpen.”, Before throwing 10 pieces of sharpened chalk at Mugman. Mugman quickly evaded all of them, with the only injury he sustained being a cut on his arm. Bendy grabbed his sword, and dashed out of the classroom, and racing up some stairs. Mugman quickly followed. Mugman made it to the top of the stairs, before he saw a hallway of abandoned lockers. Mugman walked past these lockers, as he held onto EWF tightly. “SUPRISE!”, Bendy shouted, lunging from one of the lockers, and kicking Mugman in the face, sending him flying. Mugman lands in another abandoned classroom. Bendy flies in, and bites on his sword, before saying, “Adjective: Duplicate. Time frame of twenty one seconds. Five exact copies. Starting now.” Suddenly, four more Bendys appeared beside the original Bendy, and lunged at Mugman. Mugman quickly realized he had to get rid of the four other Bendys quickly, and thought. And he thought quick. Mugman thought, “What do I do in this situation?” Suddenly, Mugmans cursed energy had focused on one of the Bendys, and Mugman instinctively said. “Dismantle.” Suddenly, the bendy clone that Mugmans energy focused on, was cut in half by one big slash caused by EWF. The other Bendys looked at the Ben-dy that was cut in half, and stopped in their tracks. They then looked at Mugman, who looked at another clone. “Cleave.”, Mugman said, and multiple grid like slices hit one of the Bendys clones, dicing the clone into cubes. “Mugman, how did you get a cursed technique with no cursed energy?”, Bendy asked, as he readied his sword.<br/>Mugman didn’t respond, and he cut through the two other Bendy clones, before saying, “Dismantle.