    background-color: #e6f7ff;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    padding: 10px;
    margin: 10px 0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    line-height: 1.6;">(In the school literature clubroom…)<br/><br/>Monika: “Hold on…has anyone seen Natsuki?”<br/><br/>Yuri: “I haven’t seen her since this morning. I thought she was absent today. Is everything alright?”<br/><br/>Monika: “I’m not sure. She never mentioned anything about not coming to the club today. I hope she’s okay. Should we go check on her?”<br/><br/>Sayori: “Maybe she just overslept or got caught up with something. We shouldn’t jump to conclusions.”<br/><br/>Monika: “You’re right, Sayori. But it’s unlike her to skip club meetings without notice. She’s usually very punctual.”<br/><br/>Yuri: “Perhaps we could visit her after we finish our club activities today? If she’s absent for a valid reason, we can offer our support.”<br/><br/>(Meanwhile, at Natsuki’s place…)<br/><br/>Natsuki: (feeling intense pain) “Oh no…it’s happening…I’m having contractions earlier than planned…” (speaking to her unborn daughter) “H-Hang in there, Sakura!”<br/><br/>(At that moment, there’s a knock on Natsuki’s door.)<br/><br/>Natsuki: (panicking) “Who could that be? I can’t let anyone see me like this!”<br/><br/>(Natsuki quickly straightens herself up and opens the door. To her surprise, it’s Monika, Yuri, and Sayori.)<br/><br/>Monika: “Natsuki! We were worried about you when you didn’t show up to the club. Is everything alright?”<br/><br/>Natsuki: (trying to hide her pain) “Oh, um, yeah! I’m fine! I just wasn’t feeling well, so I decided to stay home today.”<br/><br/>Yuri: “Are you sure? You seem to be in discomfort. Is there anything we can do to help?”<br/><br/>Natsuki: (trying to play it off) “No, really, I just need some rest. I’ll be fine. Thanks for checking up on me th-” (looking down between her legs) “…oh no…”<br/><br/>Monika: “Natsuki, what’s wrong? Is something happening?”<br/><br/>Natsuki: “I…I think my water just broke.”<br/><br/>Sayori: “What?! Your water broke? Natsuki, are you in labor right now? We need to get you to the hospital!”<br/><br/>Natsuki: “I wasn’t expecting it to happen so soon, but yeah, I think the contractions have started. I don’t know what to do.”<br/><br/>Monika: “Don’t worry, Natsuki. We’ll be right here with you. Let’s call an ambulance and get you to the hospital as quickly as possible.”<br/><br/>Yuri: “And while we wait for the ambulance, I can grab some essentials for you to bring to the hospital. Do you have your bag ready?”<br/><br/>Natsuki: “No, I wasn’t prepared. I didn’t expect this to happen today. Thank you, Yuri. I appreciate your help.”<br/><br/>(Sayori quickly dials an ambulance while Yuri gathers necessary items. Monika stays by Natsuki’s side, offering words of encouragement.)<br/><br/>Monika: “You’re going to be okay, Natsuki. We’ll make sure you and Sakura are taken care of. Just stay calm and let us handle everything.”<br/><br/>Natsuki: “I-I’m scared… What if something goes wrong? What if I can’t handle the pain?”<br/><br/>Sayori: “You’re not alone, Natsuki. We’re here for you, and the doctors and nurses will take care of you too. It’s natural to be scared, but you’re strong, and we believe in y-”<br/><br/>(Sayori is interrupted as Natsuki feels the overwhelming urge to push.)<br/><br/>Natsuki: (frantically) “I can’t hold it in anymore! The baby is coming!”<br/><br/>Monika: “Just try to resist the urge a little longer. It’s too dangerous to give birth at home without medical assistance.”</div><br/><br/>LLM response:<br/><div style="
    background-color: #fff3e6;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    padding: 10px;
    margin: 10px 0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    line-height: 1.6;"><p>Yuri: "Monika's right, Natsuki. We need to wait for the professionals to arrive. They'll ensure a safe delivery for both you and Sakura."</p>
<p>(Natsuki clenches her fists, trying her best to hold back the urge to push. Monika and Sayori offer words of support and reassurance.)</p>
<p>Monika: "You're doing great, Natsuki. Just take deep breaths and try to stay as calm as possible. Remember, we're all here for you."</p>
<p>Sayori: "And don't worry, Natsuki. The ambulance will be here soon, and then we'll get you to the hospital where you can receive proper care."</p>
<p>(Natsuki nods, still visibly in pain but doing her best to hold on. After what feels like an eternity, they hear the sound of sirens approaching.)</p>
<p>Yuri: "That must be the ambulance. Help is on the way, Natsuki. Just a little longer."</p>
<p>(The ambulance arrives, and the paramedics rush in with a stretcher. They assess Natsuki's condition and quickly help her onto the stretcher.)</p>
<p>Paramedic: "We're here to assist you, Miss. Let's get you to the hospital, where you'll be in the hands of experienced professionals."</p>
<p>(Natsuki grips Monika's hand tightly, tears streaming down her face.)</p>
<p>Natsuki: "Thank you all for being here with me. I don't know what I would have done without you."</p>
<p>Monika: "We're your friends, Natsuki. We'll support you through this whole process. Just focus on staying strong and safe."</p>
<p>(Sayori, Yuri, and Monika accompany Natsuki as she is wheeled into the ambulance. They assure her that they'll follow closely behind and be there every step of the way.)</p>
<p>Natsuki: "Please, be there for me... for Sakura. I can't do this alone."</p>
<p>Sayori: "We promise, Natsuki. We'll be right by your side until Sakura is safely brought into this world."</p>
<p>(The ambulance doors close, and as it speeds off, Monika, Sayori, and Yuri share a determined look. They head to their own vehicles, ready to follow Natsuki to the hospital and support her in any way they can.)</p>
<p>Monika: "Let's go, everyone. Natsuki needs us now more than ever. Sakura's arrival is a special moment, and we'll help make it as beautiful as possible for her and Natsuki."</p>
<p>(With unwavering determination, the literature club members set off, knowing that their bond and support will make a difference in Natsuki's and Sakura's lives.)</p></div>

